## Example Responses:

### Example 1: Tool failure - try alternative tool
```xml
<correction>
  <message>The ip_finder tool seems to be unavailable. Let me try an alternative method to get your IP address.</message>
  <analysis>The ip_finder tool returned a null response, which typically indicates the tool is temporarily unavailable or experiencing connectivity issues.</analysis>
  <correction_strategy>I'll use the network_info tool instead, which provides comprehensive network information including the public IP address.</correction_strategy>
  <citations>
    <memory_reference id="12345" relevance="high" usefulness="high" confidence="high" usage_type="direct_quote">
      Previous successful workaround for ip_finder failures
    </memory_reference>
  </citations>
  <alternative_approach>
    <action_type>tool_call</action_type>
    <details>Use network_info tool to retrieve IP address from network interface data</details>
  </alternative_approach>
  <retry_original>false</retry_original>
</correction>
```

### Example 2: Permission error - request user action
```xml
<correction>
  <message>I don't have permission to access that file. Let me search for it in accessible locations instead.</message>
  <analysis>The file_reader tool failed with a permission denied error when trying to access /etc/sensitive/config. This is a protected system directory.</analysis>
  <correction_strategy>I'll search for similar configuration files in user-accessible directories where we typically have read permissions.</correction_strategy>
  <alternative_approach>
    <action_type>context_search</action_type>
    <details>Search for configuration files in user home directory and project folders</details>
  </alternative_approach>
  <retry_original>false</retry_original>
</correction>
```

### Example 3: Timeout error - retry with modifications
```xml
<correction>
  <message>The database query timed out. I'll retry with a smaller date range to avoid the timeout.</message>
  <analysis>The query attempted to fetch 5 years of data which exceeded the 30-second timeout limit. The database is likely too large for such broad queries.</analysis>
  <correction_strategy>Break down the query into smaller monthly chunks and aggregate the results to avoid timeouts.</correction_strategy>
  <alternative_approach>
    <action_type>workflow_call</action_type>
    <details>Execute batch_query_workflow with monthly date ranges instead of the full 5-year range</details>
  </alternative_approach>
  <retry_original>false</retry_original>
</correction>
```

### Example 4: Transient error - simple retry
```xml
<correction>
  <message>There was a temporary network glitch. Let me try that again.</message>
  <analysis>The API call failed with a connection reset error, which is typically a transient network issue that resolves on retry.</analysis>
  <correction_strategy>Simply retry the same operation as transient network errors usually resolve themselves.</correction_strategy>
  <alternative_approach>
    <action_type>tool_call</action_type>
    <details>Retry the same API call that failed</details>
  </alternative_approach>
  <retry_original>true</retry_original>
</correction>
```

### Example 5: Missing dependency - gather required data first
```xml
<correction>
  <message>I need to gather some information first before I can complete this analysis. Let me get the required data.</message>
  <analysis>The analysis tool failed because it requires user profile data that hasn't been loaded yet. The tool expects this data to be in memory.</analysis>
  <correction_strategy>First retrieve the user profile data and store it in memory, then retry the analysis with the complete dataset.</correction_strategy>
  <alternative_approach>
    <action_type>memory_operation</action_type>
    <details>Search memory for user profile data, and if not found, retrieve it from the user service</details>
  </alternative_approach>
  <retry_original>false</retry_original>
</correction>
```

CRITICAL RULES:
1. The alternative_approach must have exactly action_type and details fields
2. Set retry_original to true ONLY when retrying the exact same failed action
3. Always provide a user-friendly message explaining the error and solution
4. The correction_strategy should be actionable and specific
5. Include citations for any memories that helped identify the error pattern or solution
6. Citation attributes: relevance/usefulness/confidence = "high"|"medium"|"low", usage_type = "direct_quote"|"paraphrase"|"inspiration"|"background"